{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and another reference is established.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GToggleNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This functionality is intended for binding "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to a proxy","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"paired references: the strong reference added by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", a strong reference is held. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" callback is called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to the proxy object should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“toggled” from strong to weak (","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" true) or weak to strong","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"is_last_ref"},{"text":" false).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", the initial state of the reverse"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"link is always strong."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is important state in the proxy object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" might","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and the object argument"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you must take care of that yourself."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be released with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLibObject","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject15BindingGroupRefV","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}]},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"kind":"article","abstract":[],"type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/objectprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObject","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef/addToggleRef(notify:data:)":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GToggleNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/BindingGroupRef":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingGroupRef"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/bindinggroupref","title":"BindingGroupRef","abstract":[{"code":"GBindingGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can be used to bind multiple properties","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from an object collectively."}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"BindingGroupRef"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/BindingGroupRef"}}}